About usermod
You can lock users with #usermod -L. It's recommended check de /etc/shadow and check the exclamation mark. 

When the user is active, you wouldn't see exclamation marks. Check test123.
When The user never did login, you would see double exclamation mark: !! Check test345.
When the user is locked, you can see one exclamatin mark: ! Check test567.

/etc/passwd:
test123:$6$WE0DXdUy$f4D300/cchugB/KE9s8/KmACp.aTq/DmeYNbSkUu7Xd38Y6DH3lic7wx1ltinbPqJCcHq3rrbRdDsDnxkw7C6.:18743:0:99999:7:::
test345:!!:18743:0:99999:7:::
test567:!$6$iD4/sDDN$C9qpiSjuNoOw8xIJeZaSjxwjOJb6zQUY67HdnqCyA/VEOMcuUa3U.Ro8xH52kpQw/.0a9pYzS1UgAMijv7vqT.:18743:0:99999:7:::



